title: Tungsten doped FeCoP2 nanoparticles embedded into carbon for highly efficient oxygen evolution reaction
content:
RSC Adv., 2024, 14,16639-16648
DOI: 10.1039/D4RA02326A, Paper
Open Access
  This article is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 3.0 Unported Licence.
Xinyao Quan, Jiajia Ma, Qianshuo Shao, Haocong Li, Lingxiang Sun, Guili Huang, Su Yan, Zhanglian Hong, Yuning Wang, Xiaoqing Wang
Tungsten-doped bimetallic phosphide nanoparticles were embedded into carbon by ball milling and phosphorisation, which required only 264 and 310 mV overpotentials to reach 10 mA cm−2 and 100 mA cm−2 current density for OER, respectively.
